        public Set<String> getAllowedMethods(CmsRequest<?> request)
        Get the allowed methods for the request. This is called on the rendered page element when CMS serves a resource. Defaults to GET, HEAD, POST.
        Specified by:

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • getResponseDataType

        public ResponseDataType getResponseDataType(CmsRequest<?> request)
        Get the response data type. This is called on the rendered page element when CMS serves a resource. This implementation returns ResponseDataType.character if the negotiated content type is text or xml i.e. text/plain, text/html, application/xhtml+xml, application/rss+xml, javascript, json. Otherwise, the implementation returns ResponseDataType.binary.
        Specified by:
        getResponseDataType in interface Negotiable
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the data type.

      • negotiateContentType

        public ContentType negotiateContentType(CmsRequest<?> request,
                                        List<LenientContentType> accept,
                                        UserAgent ua)
        Negotiate the content type. This is called on the rendered page element when CMS serves a resource. This implementation only negotiates HTML content types. If a fixed content type is set, then that is always returned.
        Specified by:
        negotiateContentType in interface Negotiable
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        accept - the accept header content types. Take care when using this as some user agents send junk.
        ua - the user agent.
        Returns:
        the content type.

      • negotiateLocale

        public Locale negotiateLocale(PageElementPath pageElementPath,
                              Set<Locale> availableLocales,
                              List<Locale> userLocales)
        Description copied from interface: Negotiable
        Negotiate the locale to render a page.
        Specified by:
        negotiateLocale in interface Negotiable
        Parameters:
        pageElementPath - the request paths that corresponds to the page being rendered,
        availableLocales - the list of available locales. Never empty.
        userLocales - the list of user locales. This could be based on the User-Agent making the request, a logged in user, a cookie, etc. The list is ordered based on preference; locales at the head of the list are preferred over locales at the end of the list.
        Returns:
        the locale.
